<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,621,1197,1223]" box="[151,621,1197,1223]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,621,1197,1223]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,621,1197,1223]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Family 
<taxonomicName authority="Piersig, 1896" authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1896" box="[247,621,1197,1223]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydryphantidae Piersig, 1896</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1269,1511]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
This family is probably a para- or polyphyletic assemblage of early derivative clades (
<bibRefCitation author="Dabert, M. &amp; Proctor, H. &amp; Dabert, J." box="[1112,1320,1269,1296]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="75 - 90" refId="ref71091" refString="Dabert, M., Proctor, H. &amp; Dabert, J. (2016) Higher-level molecular phylogeny of the water mites (Acariformes: Prostigmata: Parasitengonina: Hydrachnidiae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 101, 75 - 90. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2016.05.004" type="journal article" year="2016">
Dabert 
<emphasis box="[1197,1246,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Included genera are highly diverse in morphology and behaviour, most of them are restricted to the northern hemisphere. For more than 100 years, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Piersig" authorityYear="1896" box="[388,568,1341,1367]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydryphantidae</taxonomicName>
was known in 
<collectingCountry box="[733,868,1341,1367]" name="Madagascar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
only from stagnant-water dwelling hydryphantines (
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1893" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1893" box="[161,595,1377,1403]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incertus">
<emphasis box="[161,416,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Hydryphantes incertus</emphasis>
Koenike, 1893
</taxonomicName>
), diplodontines (
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1893" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1893" box="[787,1197,1377,1403]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Diplodontus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaubi">
<emphasis box="[787,1021,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diplodontus schaubi</emphasis>
Koenike, 1893
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1896" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1896" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Diplodontus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opimus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1372,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">D. opimus</emphasis>
Koenike, 1896
</taxonomicName>
), and mamersines (
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1898" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1898" box="[495,908,1413,1439]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testudinata">
<emphasis box="[495,733,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Mamersa testudinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koenike, F." box="[741,908,1413,1439]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="295 - 435" refId="ref72133" refString="Koenike, F. (1898) Hydrachniden-Fauna von Madagaskar und Nossi-Be. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 21 (2), 295 - 435." type="journal article" year="1898">Koenike, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[932,1109,1413,1439]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="393 - 418" refId="ref71450" refString="Gerecke, R. (2004 a) The water mites of Madagascar (Acari: Hydrachnidia): a revised list completed by original material conserved at the Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris. Zoosystema, 26 (3), 393 - 418." type="journal article" year="2004">Gerecke 2004a</bibRefCitation>
). In a revision of the African species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duges" authorityYear="1834" box="[274,412,1449,1475]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Diplodontus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,412,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diplodontus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus previously known only from species living in ponds and lakes, Gerecke (2004) described two Madagascan species adapted to running waters.
</paragraph>
